data.title: joideverve
data.content:
Spent an afternoon bouncing light around this incredible portrait of  Maori Chief Te Hapuku, painted by Gottfried Lindauer in 1877. He was the leader of Ngati Te Whatu-i-apiti, in New Zealand's Hawke's Bay region. Great to hang with another Kiwi at work. We didn't talk about the rugby once!
.
